Creating images with R

with a little bit of magick

Belinda Gao

2023-03-12

My meme

Here is a meme I recreated based on a existing meme I founded online. My meme contains two images of Drake with text to accompany his two different moves. I personally feel this meme and it’s just so close to my experience. Check it out with me!

library(magick)

# square one
drake_no <- image_read("https://media.vanityfair.com/photos/56279183d475a5ce0f58f7c8/master/pass/drake-hotline-bling-jacket-moncler.png") %>%
  image_scale(300)

# square two
blank_one <- image_blank(width = 300,
            height = 150,
            color = "#FFFFFF") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "LEARN ENGLISH TO
GET GOOD GRADES",
                 color = "#000000",
                 size = 30,
                 font = "impact",
                 gravity = "center")

# square three
drake_yes <- image_read("https://i.kym-cdn.com/entries/icons/mobile/000/020/147/drake.jpg") %>%
  image_scale(300)

# square four
blank_two <- image_blank(width = 300,
            height = 150,
            color = "#FFFFFF") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "LEARN ENGLISH TO
UNDERSTAND MEMES",
                 color = "#000000",
                 size = 30,
                 font = "impact",
                 gravity = "center")

# combining my meme
first_row <- image_append(c(drake_no, blank_one))
second_row <- image_append(c(drake_yes, blank_two))

two_rows <- c(first_row, second_row)
meme <- image_append(two_rows, stack = TRUE)

# view of the final meme
meme

# save as png
image_write(meme, "my_meme.png")

My animated GIF

This is a countdown gif I made with the words “Happy Birthday” at the end. This gif can be used to make a video clip to celebrate a birthday. And I really like the purple background. Check it out with me!

library(magick)

# frames
frame5 <- image_blank(color = "#997799",
                      width = 500,
                      height = 500) %>%
  image_annotate(text = "5",
                 size = 100,
                 color = "#FFFFFF",
                 font = "impact",
                 gravity = "center")

frame4 <- image_blank(color = "#997799",
                      width = 500,
                      height = 500) %>%
  image_annotate(text = "4",
                 size = 120,
                 color = "#FFFFFF",
                 font = "impact",
                 gravity = "center")

frame3 <- image_blank(color = "#997799",
                      width = 500,
                      height = 500) %>%
  image_annotate(text = "3",
                 size = 140,
                 color = "#FFFFFF",
                 font = "impact",
                 gravity = "center")

frame2 <- image_blank(color = "#997799",
                      width = 500,
                      height = 500) %>%
  image_annotate(text = "2",
                 size = 160,
                 color = "#FFFFFF",
                 font = "impact",
                 gravity = "center")

frame1 <- image_blank(color = "#997799",
                      width = 500,
                      height = 500) %>%
  image_annotate(text = "1",
                 size = 180,
                 color = "#FFFFFF",
                 font = "impact",
                 gravity = "center")

frame0 <- image_blank(color = "#997799",
                      width = 500,
                      height = 500) %>%
  image_annotate(text = "Happy
Birthday!!",
                 size = 80,
                 color = "#FFFFFF",
                 font = "impact",
                 gravity = "center")

# putting frames together
frames <- c(frame5, frame4, frame3, frame2, frame1, frame0)

# creating animation
animation <- image_animate(frames, fps = 1)

# view of the final animation
animation

# save as gif
image_write(animation, "my_animation.gif")
